  • Method Details

    • getSource

      IItemSource getSource()
      Get the source of the items. This will be invoked exactly once per structure element build.

      If the call chain ever got into the old API, this will be called at least once per IStructureDefinition.survivalBuild(Object, ItemStack, String, World, ExtendedFacing, int, int, int, int, int, int, int, ISurvivalBuildEnvironment, boolean) call.

    • getActor

      EntityPlayer getActor()
      Get the origin of action. This will be invoked at least once per IStructureDefinition.survivalBuild(Object, ItemStack, String, World, ExtendedFacing, int, int, int, int, int, int, int, ISurvivalBuildEnvironment, boolean) call.

    • create

      static ISurvivalBuildEnvironment create(IItemSource source, EntityPlayer actor)
      Create a default implementation with three parameters all being constants.
      Parameters:
      source - from where to drain resource
      actor - source of action
